<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2232&amp;p=18499#p18499"><![CDATA[
Maybe if the emulator wrote the SAV file to disk on every write?  Then both programs could reload the file whenever it was updated by the other.  I'm not sure exactly how that part would be done.  Disk access shouldn't be a problem, since I believe it'd be in the cache (I could be wrong though).<br /><br />It'd be kinda neat too if the controller port I/O could be rerouted to a virtual COM port, it'd be compatible with the hardware I've built so you could run the same thing on a real NES. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  It's kinda crappy for receiving bytes on the NES that way though (can't just get one randomly at any time, have to poll for it).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sun Oct 15, 2006 4:12 pm</p><hr />
